@startuml Encryption Architecture - PulseGrid

title Client-Side Encryption Architecture (AES-GCM 256-bit)

' Style principles from previous diagrams
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam actorBackgroundColor white
skinparam actorBorderColor black
skinparam participantBackgroundColor white
skinparam participantBorderColor black
skinparam arrowColor black
skinparam noteBackgroundColor white
skinparam noteBorderColor black
skinparam actorFontColor black
skinparam participantFontColor black
skinparam noteFontColor black
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam collectionsBackgroundColor white
skinparam collectionsBorderColor black
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor white
skinparam databaseBorderColor black

actor "User" as User
participant "UI Layer\n(React/Vite)" as UI
participant "CryptoService\n(Web Crypto API)" as Crypto
database "LocalStorage\n(Persistence)" as DB
participant "Third-Party API" as External

== Phase 1: Initialization (Sign Up) ==

User -> UI : Enter Password
UI -> Crypto : generateSalt()
Crypto -> Crypto : crypto.getRandomValues(16)
Crypto --> UI : Salt (Uint8Array)
UI -> DB : Store Salt (pg_salt)
note right of DB : The salt is public and used\nto re-derive the key later.

== Phase 2: Key Derivation (Login / Session Start) ==

User -> UI : Login (Enter Password)
UI -> DB : Retrieve Salt
DB --> UI : Salt
UI -> Crypto : deriveKey(password, salt)
group PBKDF2 Derivation
    Crypto -> Crypto : SHA-256 (100,000 iterations)
end
Crypto --> UI : CryptoKey (AES-GCM 256-bit)
note over UI : The key exists ONLY in volatile memory.\nIt is never persisted.

== Phase 3: Encryption & Storage (Add Credential) ==

User -> UI : Add Widget (Enter API Key/Token)
UI -> Crypto : encrypt(plainText, CryptoKey)
group AES-GCM-256
    Crypto -> Crypto : Generate IV
    Crypto -> Crypto : Encrypt Data
end
Crypto --> UI : Ciphertext (Base64 + IV)
UI -> DB : Store Encrypted Credentials (pg_creds)

== Phase 4: Decryption & Usage (Dashboard Load) ==

UI -> DB : Fetch Ciphertext
DB --> UI : Ciphertext
UI -> Crypto : decrypt(ciphertext, CryptoKey)
Crypto --> UI : Plaintext API Key
UI -> External : Authenticated Request (HTTPS)
External --> UI : JSON Data
UI -> User : Render Visualizations

== Phase 5: Security (Logout / Session End) ==

User -> UI : Logout / Close Tab
UI -> UI : Zero-out CryptoKey from memory
note right of UI : Decrypted keys are wiped.\nLocalStorage remains encrypted.

caption PulseGrid - End of Study Report: Security Architecture
@enduml
